Document: NinePatchRect
Path: godot/classes/class_ninepatchrect.rst
Summary: A control node that can scale a texture while keeping its borders intact.

Inherits: Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

NinePatchRect is a control node that can scale a texture in nine regions (center, corners, and sides). This allows you to scale a texture while keeping its borders intact, which is useful for UI elements like panels and buttons.

The texture is divided into nine regions based on the `texture_margin_left`, `texture_margin_top`, `texture_margin_right`, and `texture_margin_bottom` properties. The center region is scaled independently of the borders.

The `texture_filter` property controls how the texture is filtered when scaled.

The `draw_center` property determines whether the center region of the texture is drawn.

The `region_enabled` property enables or disables the nine-patch region drawing.

The `h_axis_count` and `v_axis_count` properties define the number of horizontal and vertical divisions for the nine-patch scaling.

The `h_offset` and `v_offset` properties control the horizontal and vertical offsets for the nine-patch regions.

The `h_scale` and `v_scale` properties determine the scaling factors for the horizontal and vertical axes of the nine-patch texture.

The `texture_repeat` property controls how the texture is repeated when scaled.

The `texture_filter` property controls the texture filtering mode.

The `texture_filter` property can be set to `TEXTURE_FILTER_NEAREST`, `TEXTURE_FILTER_LINEAR`, `TEXTURE_FILTER_LINEAR_WITH_MIPMAPS`, or `TEXTURE_FILTER_NEAREST_WITH_MIPMAPS`.

The `texture_repeat` property can be set to `TEXTURE_REPEAT_DISABLED`, `TEXTURE_REPEAT_ENABLED`, or `TEXTURE_REPEAT_MIRROR`.

The `region_enabled` property is a boolean that enables or disables the nine-patch region drawing.

The `draw_center` property is a boolean that determines whether the center region of the texture is drawn.

The `h_axis_count` and `v_axis_count` properties are integers that define the number of horizontal and vertical divisions for the nine-patch scaling.

The `h_offset` and `v_offset` properties are floats that control the horizontal and vertical offsets for the nine-patch regions.

The `h_scale` and `v_scale` properties are floats that determine the scaling factors for the horizontal and vertical axes of the nine-patch texture.

The `texture_margin_left`, `texture_margin_top`, `texture_margin_right`, and `texture_margin_bottom` properties are floats that define the margins of the texture used for nine-patch scaling.

The `texture` property is a Texture2D resource that is used for the nine-patch scaling.
